poverty, aging and diseases. Because I am young I would love to list things that seem to be a problem for the younger generation. However I would like to believe that most of the problems that affect the younger generation is a result of what their seniors are doing or if I may say what they have left the younger generation to deal with. We are slowly being drugged by alcohol. Different liquors and drugs have invaded our soils and chill them for almost everyday. There are children in almost every home that are being HIV/AIDS infected and affected. Alcohol and drugs completely destroy families, it’s the mothers and children that have to suffer the consequences of a one night stand, long after the man has left. Poverty is leaving us bitter and with a switched outlook towards life. Alcohol is forbidden in my community and I think women should not abuse it (note: I am not a religious person) Most men in my community do not beat women but alcohol is what causes some men to cheat on their wives, it is what causes fathers to leave their children to die of unfortunate circumstances . It is what leaves young girls to lose their dignity. Poverty and lack of accountability from my government are the core reasons for the high rate of alcohol and drug consumption. There is no sense of being something in this life, and there never will be.

Madika Daniel Matse is 28 years old, studied hands through the law and lived in an isolated village in Botswana called Havele Gweta
